  <h1 id='header'>Sustainable cities and communities: making our settlements better places</h1>
  <p id='txt'>Often now, we find ourselves in an increasingly complex society that seems to further stray from social, environmental and economic goals. As seen with high housing prices, places that become impossible to navigate without personal transportation, and dwindling resources that are available to people living in these communities. <br></br>To do this, we will go over what it means to make our cities and communities more sustainable.
  </p>
  <div id = 'imageDiv'>
    <img id = 'image' src="sustainablecity.jpg">
  </div>
  <br></br>
  <p id='txt'>When talking about making a city more sustainable, it means managing and planning that the city so that it addresses problems involving the enviornment, the economic impact and the social aspects. Such that the city can meet the needs of its popualtion, while not compromising the needs of its future citizens. It is projected that by 2050, 70% of the world's population will be living in a city. So it is very important that the cities and communites we already live in become more sustainable in order to support the increasing population of these cities. In order to lessen the strain on the environment's, people's, and the economy's health.<br></br>To investigate areas of key interest for sustainable cities/communities, how we can make cities and communties more sustainable, and what effects those would have, use the navigation menu to explore the factors of sustainable cities, actions we can take, and the effects of sustainable cities.</p>
